description: OverLord is dead and all of the bad guys in Chicago are at war to decide who takes his place as the head of the Vicious Circle! This groundbreaking series of issues firmly established Erik Larsen as one of the greatest cartoonists in the comic book medium. The Savage Dragon must face his biggest challenges ever! Includes an extensive sketchbook section that gives a fascinating peak behind the curtains with one of the most creative minds in the comic book field. Amazing art!

description:
Reprinting the one of the most controversial comics ever...plus a few of the runners up! Starting with Rapture's proposal to Dragon and ending with the birth of their illegitimate love child-this one has it all! This volume features appearances from the Maxx, Freak Force, WildStar, Spawn, the F-word, plus the greatest battle of all time - God vs. the Devil.

Introduction done by Jim Steranko.

description: The first serialized installment in a critically-acclaimed graphic novel trilogy spanning the brilliant and dangerous years of the Weimar Republic of Germany. Artists, journalists, communists, fascists, police, poets, lovers and workers cross paths while they dance the decadent city of Berlin into the arms of growing fascism. Life is not a cabaret for the denizens of Europe's fascinating city of stones.
name: City of Stones, Part 1

description: The time is October 1928, and Kurt Severing is witness to an event where the seething animosity between the fascists and the "reds" violently erupts.
name: City of Stones, Part 3

description:
The first collection of the new BIRDS OF PREY series! The team struggles to stop bombs from killing the citizens of GOTHAM CITY. Plus: Is BLACK CANARY guilty of murder? Collects BIRDS OF PREY #1-7!

THE SIRENS OF THE NIGHT

One is wanted for a murder. The other is one the run for knowing too much. Together, Black Canary and Starling work in Gotham City, taking down the villains other heroes can't touch. But now, as a grizzled newspaper reporter threatens to expose them, the two get sucked into a nightmare involving stolen pharmaceuticals, terrorist for hire and killers in stealth suits who can appear --- and disappear --- at will.

Realizing that Gotham City's citizens are in grave danger, Black Canary recruits Katana, a vengeful samurai, and notorious bioterrorist Poison Ivy. Will the Birds of Prey be able to work together to save Gotham?

BIRDS OF PREY: TROUBLE IN MIND (collecting issues 1-7 of the New 52 series) is hard hitting story by mystery novelist DUANE SWIERCZYNSKI (Expiration Date, Cable) and artist JESUS SAIZ (THE BRAVE AND THE BOLD).
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Birds of Prey: Trouble in Mind

description:
Two FIRESTORMS make their explosive returns in the DC COMICS – THE NEW 52 series! As RONNIE RAYMOND and JASON RUSCH learn to work together, they learn that they are hardly the only FIRESTORMS! Collecting THE FURY OF FIRESTORM: THE NUCLEAR MEN #1-6!

Back Blurb

A STORM IS COMING...AND NO ONE IS SAFE!

The firestorm protocols were meant to bring about world peace. Instead, they have created some of the most dangerous living weapons known to man.

A football star and a straight-A student, Ronnie Raymond and Jason Rusch have absolutely nothing in common. But after an attack on their high school they soon find themselves bonded together in ways they never could have imagined. Now, both posses unlimited nuclear powers...as Firestorm!

Using powers they barely understand, Ronnie and Jason must protect themselves and those closest to them from corporate mercenaries and rogue Firestorm terrorist. In order to do that, the duo will need to put aside their mutual dislike and work together. But taking out enemies isn't the only reason Jason and Ronnie need to get along. When these two get angry at each other, it unleashes the Firestorm known as Fury...

...and Fury may cause the end of life as we know it.

Fan-favorite creators GAIL SIMONE (BATGIRL), ETHAN VAN SCIVER (FLASH: REBIRTH) and YILDIRAY CINAR (LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES) fuse their creative powers and reinvent the Nuclear Man in THE FURY OF FIRESTORM - THE NUCLEAR MEN: GOD PARTICLE (collecting issues #1-6).
name: Volume 1

volume.name: The Fury of Firestorm: Nuclear Men: God Particle

description: Meat Cake continues with Dame Darcy's lovable cast of miscreants in their one page gags and multi-page stories. Hindrance and Perfidia the two headed twins set to see and run into Effluvia. Richard Dirt and beau Wax Wolf devise a devious (and sexy) way to ride the bus on the cheap to describe just a few of the tasty tidbits here.

This issue includes Batman #3 & Batman: The Dark Knight #3.

As Bruce digs deeper into the mystery of the recent owl murders, he soon finds himself face to face with a shocking enemy – an enemy the Wayne family has secretly been at war with for centuries. Be there for the first shots of the war for the soul of Gotham City. Friends will become deadly enemies and secrets will be revealed – revelations that will change the Bat-family forever.

A wave of fear washes across Gotham City as a mysterious toxin radically alters the bodies of its criminals, sending crazed villains into the streets and stretching the resources of the police department. Can Batman and his vigilante partners follow the clues and uncover the perpetrator's real identity? And when one fabled hero is stricken by the poison, the trail will point to the mysterious White Rabbit.
name: La Treceava Hora/Atrápame si Puedes

description:
This issue includes Justice League #3.

*The name in the issue mistakenly says "Parte Dos" instead of "Parte Tres"

The superstar team of writer Geoff Johns and artist Jim Lee continue to make history as they unleash the amazing Amazon, Wonder Woman, who joins the battle against a bizarre threat! And the not-yet World's Greatest Heroes need all the help they can get! This issue is also offered as a special combo pack edition, polybagged with a redemption code for a digital download of the issue.
name: Justice League Parte Tres*

description:
This issue includes Batman: Arkham City #2

Amid the protests of both human rights groups and Bruce Wayne, a new Arkham rises. The Joker is scheduled to be its first inmate, but not if Harley Quinn has anything to say about it. Meanwhile, Batman's suspicions lead him to investigate just who is really behind this new, more sprawling asylum and what their motivations might be.
name: Batman Arkham City #2: Innovador

description: The adventures of Ashley J. Williams continue! Now that the 'Long Road Back Home' has been taken, it's time to head back to 'Home Sweet Hell'! Ash is back in a world mostly of his own making - back in the S-Mart and checking prices on toasters and girdles. Only thing is, the demons are conspiring and Ash is, well, Ash doesn't remember anything. And because he doesn't remember anything, heading out to that cabin in the woods after a long work week sounds just fine to him... welcome to Hell, Ash! Again!
name: Home Sweet Hell

description:
In the final chapter of this series, Bruce Wayne completes his improbable recovery from his broken back and is ready to resume his role as Gotham's protector. But Jean Paul Valley, the man who now patrols the night as a vicious and violent Batman, is not willing to give up his new identity. Driven to the brink of madness by inner demons, the new Batman seeks to destroy Bruce as they meet in mortal combat. But in the end, Bruce defeats Jean Paul both mentally and physically and reclaims his legendary cape and cowl.

This new edition includes many chapters of KNIGHTFALL never before collected.

Collects Batman #509-514, Batman: Shadow of the Bat #29-34, Detective Comics #676-681, Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight #62-63, Robin #8-13 and Catwoman #12-13.
name: Volume Three: Knightsend
